rules:
- id: rule-promotion-requires-evidence
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Pattern promotion to core must be supported by strong evidence, preferably
    from multiple sources or systems, to ensure foundational stability.
  title: Rule Promotion Requires Evidence
- id: rule-system-proposes-architect-decides
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be proposed by the system and explicitly
    handled (accepted, rejected, or deferred) by an architect to maintain human-in-the-loop
    control.
  title: Rule System Proposes Architect Decides
- id: rule-heuristic-patterns-require-signals
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Every heuristic-derived pattern must include at least one linked signal
    as evidence to ensure traceability and grounding in observed behavior.
  title: Rule Heuristic Patterns Require Signals
- id: rule-workflow-execution-model-compliance
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All runtime-native workflows must conform to the CAS Workflow Execution
    Model, maintaining strict separation between orchestration, reasoning, and knowledge
    access.
  title: Rule Workflow Execution Model Compliance
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-adr-single-source-of-truth
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture decisions must be recorded and updated exclusively in decision
    records (ADR), with all other representations being derived from them.
  title: Rule Adr Single Source Of Truth
- id: rule-precedence-hierarchy
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines the precedence model (Global > Project > Prompt) for resolving
    conflicts and ensuring predictable system behavior.
  title: Rule Precedence Hierarchy
- id: rule-decision-status-drives-stage
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The lifecycle stage of any architecture item must be derived from its decision
    status; items not marked as 'accepted' cannot be considered DONE.
  title: Rule Decision Status Drives Stage
- id: rule-architecture-work-authority
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture Work acts as the authoritative source for planning state;
    generated artifacts must derive their status from it.
  title: Rule Architecture Work Authority
- id: rule-generated-artifacts-not-authoritative
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Generated governance artifacts should summarize authoritative sources but
    must not become the primary source of truth themselves.
  title: Rule Generated Artifacts Not Authoritative
- id: rule-do-not-merge-across-architectural-layers
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Patterns must not be consolidated across different architectural layers
    to preserve clarity between governance, execution, and reliability concerns.
  title: Rule Do Not Merge Across Architectural Layers
- id: rule-aem-consistency-with-decisions
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Ensures the Architecture Evolution Map (AEM) reflects and never contradicts
    existing Architecture Decision Records (ADR).
  title: Rule Aem Consistency With Decisions
- id: rule-decisions-must-be-persisted
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be persisted as structured ADRs before
    they are reflected in the AEM or other artifacts.
  title: Rule Decisions Must Be Persisted
- id: rule-core-patterns-must-be-foundational
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Core patterns are reserved for foundational architectural primitives rather
    than specific strategies or context-specific implementations.
  title: Rule Core Patterns Must Be Foundational
- id: rule-language-semantic-contract
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Establishes strict semantic definitions for intent, state, and lifecycle
    terminology across all architecture artifacts.
  title: Rule Language Semantic Contract
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-decision-schema-must-be-structured
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Decisions must be expressed using a structured YAML schema rather than
    unstructured text to enable machine processing and consistency.
  title: Rule Decision Schema Must Be Structured
- id: rule-patterns-born-as-supporting
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All patterns must be initially created as 'supporting' to ensure they are
    validated by evidence before potential promotion to 'core'.
  title: Rule Patterns Born As Supporting
- id: rule-shared-knowledge-workspace
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Projects must utilize the shared Knowledge Workspace and are prohibited
    from duplicating workspace-level governance structures.
  title: Rule Shared Knowledge Workspace
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-pattern-decision-lifecycle-alignment
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Maintains a clear distinction and consistent mapping between pattern knowledge
    evolution and governance decision status.
  title: Rule Pattern Decision Lifecycle Alignment
- id: rule-signal-promotion-criteria
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines mandatory criteria (recurrence, impact, reusability, stability)
    for promoting a candidate signal to an architectural pattern.
  title: Rule Signal Promotion Criteria
summary:
  global_rules: 19
  project_rules: 0
  total_rules: 19
